# Next.js App Router Rules

- Prefer Server Components by default; use `use client` only when required by browser APIs or local interactivity.
- Keep data fetching on the server when possible; avoid client-side fetches for initial page state.
- Use route-level `loading` and `error` boundaries for async and failure states.
- Prefer Server Actions (with input validation) for mutations over ad hoc API calls.
- Keep layouts/pages focused; move reusable logic to package-level modules.
- Use Suspense for async UI boundaries and avoid blocking the entire route tree.
